{"id":151646,"link":"https://chinadigitaltimes.net/chinese/2011/05/googlefacebook称do-not-track威胁加州经济/","date":"2011-05-11T05:00:39Z","modified":"2011-05-11T05:00:39Z","title":"Google/Facebook称Do-Not-Track威胁加州经济","content":"<p>搜索巨人和社交巨人罕见的立场一致：他们告诉加州的立法议员，如果通过Do-Not-Track法案，其后果将是加州的经济受到威胁。 Do-Not-Track最早是Mozilla提出的，允许用户主动向服务器发送声明，表示希望“退出”被跟踪。目前苹果Safari、Firefox 4和IE 9都支持Do-Not-Track，但Chrome还没有加入。加州的Do-Not-Track提案将要求加州互联网公司为消费者提供一个“退出”的隐私保护机制。Google、Facebook、Yahoo、Amex、Acxiom、Experian、Allstate、时代华纳、MPAA、ESA等企业和组织在一封抗议信（PDF）中声称，Do-Not-Track法案将为网络经济创造一个不必要的，不可执行的以及违宪的监管负担，将会产生负面影响，使网民更容易受到安全威胁。<img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://solidot.org.feedsportal.com/c/33236/f/556826/s/14b571a7/mf.gif\" width=\"1\" /></p>\n<div>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"http://res.feedsportal.com/viral/sendemail2.html?title=Google%2FFacebook%E7%A7%B0Do-Not-Track%E5%A8%81%E8%83%81%E5%8A%A0%E5%B7%9E%E7%BB%8F%E6%B5%8E&#038;link=http%3A%2F%2Fit.solidot.org%2Farticle.pl%3Fsid%3D11%2F05%2F10%2F0146243%26amp%3Bfrom%3Drss\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/images/emailthis2.gif\" /></a></td>\n<td valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"http://res.feedsportal.com/viral/bookmark.cfm?title=Google%2FFacebook%E7%A7%B0Do-Not-Track%E5%A8%81%E8%83%81%E5%8A%A0%E5%B7%9E%E7%BB%8F%E6%B5%8E&#038;link=http%3A%2F%2Fit.solidot.org%2Farticle.pl%3Fsid%3D11%2F05%2F10%2F0146243%26amp%3Bfrom%3Drss\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/images/bookmark.gif\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/101091732705/u/49/f/556826/c/33236/s/14b571a7/a2.htm\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/101091732705/u/49/f/556826/c/33236/s/14b571a7/a2.img\" /></a></p>\n<div>\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/solidot?a=6d1CVFLWLus:9Cp2sBqQHtY:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/solidot?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" /></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/solidot?a=6d1CVFLWLus:9Cp2sBqQHtY:7